content.description: A classic. Begins with a steep offset bit of rock, then up a slab on jugs to a headwall below the obvious high roof. Watch the end of the rope as it takes 28 meters of your 60.
content.location: Begins with an offset seam to nearly the highest point of the wall.

content.description:
This climb starts in by greeting to a left facing flake. Once at the top of the flake, step left to get directly under the bolt line.

Climb straight up to the anchors using pockets and edges.
content.protection: 6 bolts plus mossy hooks at the anchors.
content.location: Route is between SuperDog! and Doodles.

climbs.name: Super-Dog!
climbs.fa: Willow Tostrup-Wells and Sam Lightner Jr

content.description: Super-Dog! is a fun climb, being steep and loaded with good holds. It's bolted for beginner climbers and makes a good first lead.
content.location: Find the start just left of the start of Doodles. Follow the bolts to an anchor that is about 5 feet left of the Doodles anchor.

content.description: Fun slabby route, starts pretty steep and gets easier along the way. Winds along faces pointing in three directions, which keeps it interesting. I'd put the crux at the first couple moves.
content.location: First problem (counting R->L) on Camel Jockey Wall. Easiest to locate by noticing it's all by itself (nothing for ~50 ft on either side) between Harvest Moon Wall and the rest of Camel Jockey.

content.description: Stem the corner formed between the main wall and the giant flake the from the top of the flake climb the blunt arete to an anchor above the small roof.
content.location: Begins in the corner on the right end of the Zozzone

content.description: About 20 feet right(climber's right) of Put Down Your Ducky (5.8) is this short bouldery route. Climb the bulge/shield feature on excellent rock using sidepulls, underclings and crimps. I recommend pre-hanging as many draw as you can, especially on the second hangar as some may find it a bit difficult to clip. Really fun sequence up to the fourth bolt and then cruiser jugs on less than vertical terrain past the fifth and final bolt and on to the anchors.
content.protection: Quickdraws. Five(5) bolts and a set of Fixed ring anchors.
content.location: Dutch Rudder is located on climber's right from Put Down Your Ducky on Sink's Main Wall. These two routes are just up canyon from all of the moderates located to the left of Killer Cave. The next route to the right from Rudder is Global Warm-up.

climbs.name: Doodles
climbs.fa: Sam Lightner, jr and Dennis Van Denbos

content.description: Follow a series of flakes for three bolts then step left and move up the face on very good holds. Brand new so there is some loose crunchy stuff, but it is cleaning up well.
content.location: Far left side of the wall up the retained steps.

content.description: Climb up the middle of the wall in the broken corner. Rock looks dubious, but it is pretty solid. Steep jugs at the end.
Climb up the outside of the giant flake, trending right to a hard move then up an arete and back left. Finish on the last half of Frogger.
content.location: Far right end of the Zozone on a giant flake.
